HEADWORD: Conciergerie
<hw>Con`cier`ge*rie"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office or lodge of a concierge or
janitor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A celebrated prison, attached to the Palais de
Justice in Paris.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

